{
  "texts": [
    "In this study, six co-citation clusters were identified using the log-likelihood ratio (LLR) technique.",
    "This was possible since the clusters created by LLR had excellent quality, with high intra-class and low inter-class similarity.",
    "Additionally, based on the uniqueness and coverage of each cluster, LLR chooses a label based on the keywords of the texts cited in each cluster.",
    "Cluster labelling quality is determined by the variety, depth, and breadth of terms formed from keywords in articles.",
    "The label supplied for each cluster identifies the focus of that cluster."
  ]
}